            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div><em><strong>Figure 2:</strong></em> <em>Website impersonating “Wiser University” (Source: Recorded Future)</em></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h6>Suspected Testing Infrastructure</h6>
        <p>Although most IP addresses associated with the Type 1 staging infrastructure are announced by AS202015, as shown in <strong>Appendix B</strong>, Insikt Group also identified a small subset announced by other ASNs that host the same websites (see <strong>Table 4</strong>). On average, approximately one such IP address appears to be established each month. Notably, most of these IP addresses appear to geolocate to Russia, and the same ASNs are consistently reused within the same timeframe.</p>
